org.sakaiproject.metaobj.utils.mvc.intf

Interface CustomCommandController

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Controller
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AddCriterionController, AddLayoutController, AddLevelController, AddScaffoldingController, AddStructuredArtifactDefinitionController, AddStyleController, AddXmlElementController, BaseListObjectController, CommentListController, EditStructuredArtifactDefinitionController, EditXmlElementController, FormDeleteController, ImportStructuredArtifactDefinitionController, InviteFeedbackConfirmationController, ListEvaluationItemController, MultiModelViewController, RemoveExpectationConfirmationController, RemoveLevCritConfirmationController, ResourceDeleteController, SubmitCellConfirmationController

    public interface CustomCommandController
extends Controller
    Use this controller when you need to override the way the backing object is created. If all you are doing is return new MyBackingObject() you won't need to implement this, Spring will handle that for you. Do not use this method to populate helping data into the model. This method does not get called if there is an error in validation. If you rely on this information for putting stuff in the request, you will not have it there in the case of validation error. If you need to put helping data in the model, implement FormController's referenceData method.
    Author:
    John Ellis (john.ellis@rsmart.com), John Bush (john.bush@rsmart.com)
